<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773491>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 4. Identity plate of the Actinidia faveolata wholeplant. The seed is the unique available fossil part. a) fossil seed of Actinidia faveolata from the Stura di Lanzo Fossil Forest (Martinetto et al. 2007a), Piacenzian of northern Italy. b) foliage remains lacking. c) remains of woody axes lacking. d) pollen remains lacking. e) modern seed of Actinidia arguta (from Hiroshima Bot. Garden), with a structure closely similar to Actinidia faveolata. f) aspect of a living plant of A. arguta with fruits and leaves, Botanical Garden of the Faculty of Science, Charles University, Prague. Scale bar 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773491/files/figure.png" .

